\ SAMPLES.DOC           Sample source file for TCOM     by Tom Zimmer

  TCOM includes several example source files to illustrate various
features available in TCOM, and to provide some utilities you might find
useful. Here then is a list of the included files and their features:

        ALLSPECS        A utility file, that builds a list of all of the
                        files on the disk given a starting directory.
                        Used by LOOK.

        BANNER          Displays messages on the screen in large
                        letters, illustrates table creation.

        BEGTIME         A utility to assist in keeping track of your
                        consulting time. See the source for details.
                        written by Robert Smith.

        BINEDIT         A Binary File Editor with search and modify
                        capability in either ascii of hex formats.

        CAPSOFF         An example of how to make a very small program
                        that doesn't do any Forth, or any
                        initialization, just a single code word to turn
                        off the CAPS LOCK key.

        CARD            A small card file program, uses BLOCK, pulldown
                        MENUS, and the DOS SHELL feature of TCOM.

        CLOCK           A nice visual clock program, does extensive
                        cursor control.  Written by Jerry Modrow

        COLOURS         Displays a screen full of colors.  Useful for
                        selecting screen colors that go well together in
                        a program.  Written by Mike Mayo

        CSUM            A little program that adds all the bytes in a
                        specified file together, and display a 32 bit
                        checksum result.

        CURSOR          A program that turns on the computers cursor.
                        Also illustrates the use of the /0INIT option.

        D               A directory display program, shows one or
                        more sets of files matching the file specs given
                        on the command line.

        DDUP            A Disk DUPlicator example, compilable with either
                        F-PC or TCOM.  Reads a disk image (1.2meg or
                        1.4meg) into a hard disk file, and then allows
                        quick duplication (49 seconds/preformatted disk).

        DECIDE          A simple little example of how to prompt the
                        user for a response to a yes/no question, and
                        set the errorlevel to a number corresponding to
                        the response.

        DESCR           A utility for 4DOS users. It extracts the first
                        line comment out of a specified source file, and
                        sets the 4DOS description according to the text.

        DOODLE          A program that illustrates the graphics support
                        provided by TCOM, and the new MOUSE support just
                        added to TCOM. 320 by 200 by 16 colors.

        DRAW            Another program that illustrates the graphics
                        support provided by TCOM, and the new MOUSE
                        support just added to TCOM. 640 by 480 by 16
                        colors.

        EMMTEST         A program to illustrate the interface to the
                        Expanded Memory Manager.  Requires Expanded
                        memory on the computer to run.  Also contains
                        some documentation on the expanded memory
                        managers calls.

        ENDTIME         A utility to assist in keeping track of your
                        consulting time. See the source for details.
                        written by Robert Smith.

        FILTER          A file filter program, illistrates how to do use
                        DOS's standard I/O to process a file, and direct
                        the processed file out to another program of
                        file. Also shows how to use buffered I/O to
                        speed performance.

        FLOATER         A simple example file on floating point usage.

        FORM            Sends a FORMFEED to the printer. Another example
                        of how to make a very small program.

        G               Go to a directory specified by an alias in the
                        file GO.DAT. A quick directory changer.

        GCLOCK          A graphic clock program, runs in 640x480x16 VGA
                        video mode.

        GLOBAL          A global editor.  Allows a string replacement to
                        be performed through each or all occurances in
                        one or more files.

        GSS             Graphic Screen Saver, draw squares on a
                        640x480x16 graphics screen very quickly.

        GT              Graphics Test, performs a flood fill in VGA mode
                        $12 (640x480x16), filling graphic memory with
                        colors black through white, and then displays the
                        resulting performance figure in millions of
                        pixels/second.  Really just tests video memory
                        bandwidth.

        INDEX           A program that compiles index files for the
                        hyper-text feature of the Z editor.

        KOKO            A graphics program written by Konrad Koler, as
                        modified for TCOM by Tom Zimmer.

        LINES           A simple graphics program, draws lines on the
                        screen.

        LINESCAN        A random graphics line scanning program, runs in
                        640x350x16.

        LINEWALK        A random graphics line walking program, runs in
                        640x350x16. A variation on LINESCAN, and a
                        non-TSR version of TSRLINES.

        LOOK            A file scanner, searches files specified for a
                        particular character sequence. Shows how to use
                        LINEREAD, and perform various file operations.
                        Can search many files VERY FAST. Needs
                        ALLSPECS.SEQ to compile.

        MAN486          Dr. Ting's Mandelbrot program.  Requires a 80386
                        with a 80387 coprocessor or a 80486 to run.  Very
                        fast screen update, with much assembly language.

        MIDNIGHT        The towers of hanoi example from Peter Midnight.

        NOW             A program to display the current time from the
                        computers clock.

        PASCAL          An updated implementation of the TINY pascal
                        compiler I (Tom Zimmer) wrote several years ago.
                        This version translates the example file
                        PASX.PAS into Forth source and displays the
                        results on the console. you can also use I/O
                        redirection to send output to a file. The
                        resulting output file can then be TCOMed into a
                        runable program. A very simple Pascal
                        translator.

        PROFILE         Allows profiling TCOM applications to determine
                        where your programs are spending most of their
                        time.

        PROMPTER        An example of how to prompt the user for
                        information, and then pass that information off
                        to another program on the command line. Uses the
                        DOS shell capability of TCOM.

        PUSHCR          A utilitiy that allows a string of keys (upto 12
                        characters) to be pushed into the keyboard
                        buffer, to be used by whatever program is
                        executed on the following line of the batch file
                        inwhich PUSHCR is used.

        RESTART         Reboot the computer, with either a warm or cold
                        parameter.  Donated by a german user.

        RINGS           Draws random ring like images on the screen in
                        graphics mode 640x350x16.

        RS232IB         An example that provides RS232 serial buffered
                        I/O routines to either TCOM or F-PC. For TCOM,
                        it turns into a very simple terminal program.

        SAMPLE          The proverbial "Hello World" program, is an
                        example of how to use some of the commandline
                        options in TCOM, and how to make a very small
                        program.

        SET50           A very small program written in assembly language
                        that switches a VGA to 50 line mode, and an EGA
                        to 43 line mode.

        SETMODE         A little utility to change to video mode of your
                        computer to the HEX mode number following SETMODE
                        on the DOS command line.

        SHELL           A mini file shell, uses the popup file selection
                        box and shells out to DOS to execute programs,
                        or calls up the SZ editor to browse and edit
                        files. Also shows how to minimize the memory
                        usage of a program.

        SPLAT           A little program that displays a pseudo random
                        sequence of multi-colored dots on the screen,
                        and will wait for the user to enter a password
                        before letting the program terminate.

        SSBLIT          Display the SAMSUNG logo in graphics mode using a
                        BITBLIT (memory to screen bit image transfer).
                        Runs in 640x350x16 graphics mode.

        STRIP           An example program to illustrate how to write a
                        program that processes all the lines of a text
                        file and writes them, out to a new file after
                        processing.

        SZ              An editor smaller than my Z editor. SZ for Small
                        Zimmers editor.

        TERMSTAY        *** NOT A COMPLETE PROGRAM ***
                        An example, illustrating how to make a very
                        simple terminate and stay resident program.  You
                        must insert your own code to detect a key press,
                        or other event to activate the resident program.
                        Will not compile as provided.

        TETRA           A simplified version of the game of TETRIS.
                        Still quite fun to play though. Written by Marc
                        Hawley, and very slightly modified for TCOM by
                        Tom Zimmer.

        TEXTFORM        A simple text formatter, recognizes embeded
                        . (dot) commands and generates formatted text
                        output to the screen. Can be redirected.

        TIMEFILE        A special utility that can be useful in making
                        automatic backup batch files.  Creates a unique
                        date and time related filename and allows easy
                        creation of a batch file to perform a backup
                        using the filename.

        TIMEIT          Uses the TIMEIT functions to make a program that
                        measures the execution time of a DOS commandline
                        following TIMEIT on its DOS commandline.

        TSR             A relatively simple number conversion TSR
                        (Terminate and Stay Resident) programming
                        example.

        TSRCLOCK        A TSR that displays the current time in the
                        upper right corner of the screen.

        TSRIDLE         A TSR that invokes a batch file IDLE.BAT after no
                        keys are pressed on the keyboard for ten minutes.
                        Will only actually invoke IDLE.BAT if there is
                        some available DOS memory for the DOS SHELL.  You
                        will need to create IDLE.BAT to contain the name
                        of the screen saver you want to invoke after ten
                        minutes.

        TSRKOKO         A TSR and enhanced version of Konrad Koller's
                        fractal graphics program.  Scroll lock pops it
                        up, and controlls whether it auto cycles through
                        multiple designes, or continues to develop the
                        current design.  Space redraws.

        TSRLINES        A TSR that displays lines in graphics mode after
                        no keys are pressed for 10 minutes. A TSR version
                        of LINEWALK.

        TSRPAL          A TSR to allow selecting random color palletes
                        at each press of Scroll Lock.  Gaudy but fun!

        VGATING         VGA video mode 13 hex graphics by Dr. Ting.  Used
                        by MAN486.SEQ.

        ZIF             A conditional utility file written for Jerry
                        Boutelle, to provide a "IF-NOT" function. The
                        opposite of "IF". An alias is also provided in
                        the form "0=IF". This file can be used on both
                        F-PC and TCOM.

        ZIM             An experimental file compression utility. Builds
                        a common word table, and replaces words with
                        tokens in the .ZIM file.  Works pretty well for
                        Forth source files.

        ZLIST           A file viewer, works with very large files by
                        keeping only part of the file in memory. There
                        is almost no limit to to the size of a file that
                        can be viewed. ZLIST has been tested on files
                        over 32 megabytes.  Searching can be kind of slow
                        on a file that large of course.

        ZMOVE           A simple file transfer utility for moving files
                        between two computers connected between COM1:.
                        Needs RS232IB.SEQ to compile.

        ZRAY            A simple memory monitor TSR. Allows poping up a
                        window that will show what is in a specified
                        area of computer memory.

        ZTREE           A utility that displays a sum of all files in
                        each directory. Useful for finding out where all
                        your disk space is going.

        ZZ              ZZ is a sort of shell program that can tie
                        several disparit programs together into a
                        workable environment. Essentially it uses a
                        ZZ.CFG file to dictate what programs it works
                        with, and uses the SZ or Z editor as a director
                        that issues ZZ commands through a ZZ.CMD file to
                        call other programs like compilers and debuggers
                        with commandline parameters. See ZZ.TXT for a
                        bit more information.

  In addition to the above listed files, TCOMSAMP.ZIP also contains some
extra files used either by TCOM or by other sample programs.

        INDEX.CFG       A configuration file for INDEX.

        LOOK.COM
        LOOK.DOC        An executable copy of LOOK, and the
                        documentation for LOOK.

        LS86.SEQ
        LS1.SEQ
        LS2.SEQ
        DA86.SEQ        The files that makeup the LS86.COM program used
                        by TCOM to generate listings of TCOM compiles.

        PASX.PAS        A simple pascal example source file for PASCAL.

        TESTALL.BAT     A batch file to compile all (or at least most) of
                        the sample programs included with TCOM. TCOM must
                        have been previously installed properly.

        ZZ.CFG
        ZZ.TXT          A configuration file for ZZ, and a documentation
                        file for ZZ.


